editorialSummary.text: Fast-food chain serving signature beef, chicken & fish sliders, plus extras such as onion rings.

originalText.text: The food took about an hour to make. Super busy location. The staff was friendly to me but I was watching. She was sassy to about some other people. Maybe they were being rude too. The food was great after getting it. Washrooms they need to buzz you in. Place is kinda not so clean but I liked the sliders.

originalText.text: When I arrived there were already several people waiting for their food. The soda dispenser was broken so Could not get your own drinks/refills. There were only 2 employees. 1 doing the front register and the drive through while the other was on the grill. Took about 30 minutes to get my food, and people before me were still waiting.

originalText.text:
Honestly I feel like I was here at the worst time. It felt super tense and everytime more customers came in it felt more tense. The workers here seemed super stressed out but I want to acknowledge that they did a great job of dealing with so many people in the restaurant. There were a few mistakes for some orders (recognized and fixed quickly by staff) while others were spot on that even the customer forgot "Oh yeah I ordered that" I would really want whoever the owner is to know that your team deserves some recognition for working hard and dealing with such an influx of constant customers and huge orders. Not to mention however many people were ordering delivery.

Food wise: decent. Sliders. Can't really say more or less about it than a good snack if you order a bit or a full on eating contest for one person ordering 2 family meals or something. Not a fan of the plain stuff and the 1927 or whatever sliders still weren't something I cared about. Fries were solid. I only ate here to fulfill the experience of seeing the Harold and Kumar movie where they went to white Castle and I'm good.
